<StringTableFile>
  <Name>conversations\03_defiance_bay_ondra_gift\03_cv_weyd</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>54</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd's eyes are red-rimmed and unfocused. He stares into a filthy mug as if searching for something. He shivers and takes another drink.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>His eyes are filled with shame and self-loathing. "What do you want from me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Grab Weyd by the collar.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Tap Weyd on the shoulder.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your son is dead. Derrin was defending one of the women here from a couple of thugs."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your son's missing. You'd better explain what you're doing here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You might as well have killed him yourself. In fact, that's what I'm going to tell everyone here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I was taking the boy fishing, and I just wanted to stop on the way for a drink. A quick one. So I told him to wait for me outside. I only meant to stay a few minutes, but by the time I came out, he was gone."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd seems to stare through you. "My... my boy died while I was here? Odda, my wife... she always said I'd come to no good, but I never thought..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You can change. If you want to be worthy of him, go home and take care of the family you still have."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You need to tell Odda what happened."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>He draws a deep breath and looks at the half-empty mug in front of him. With a shaking hand, he pushes it away. "I don't know if you're right. But I'll try to pull myself together enough to find out."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You WHAT? Maybe it's no less than I deserve, but one of these days, I hope you get what's coming to you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Thank you for finding my boy, and thank you for talking me into coming home. I wish to the gods it hadn't taken me this long to learn."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can't a man drink in peace?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Lie] "Derrin boarded a Vailian ship. He left Defiance Bay in search of something more."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What's the use? It's over. Our son is dead. She'll never have me back. This is where I belong."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Never mind."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Something more than a life of cleaning up after me, I reckon." He pushes himself unsteadily from the bar. "I'd better tell Odda. She'll forgive me one day, and, gods willing, so will my boy."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It's better this way, I'm sure. He'll go on to be a better man than me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd turns back to his drink and takes a long gulp.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That can't be changed now. You have to decide to move forward with your life."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd laughs bitterly. "You've obviously never lost a child. My future is right here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>He looks into his mug. "And at this rate, it will be a short one."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd stumbles out of the bar, casting a final, contemptuous glare over his shoulder.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd takes a swing, his fist sailing a foot from your ear. His momentum sends him crashing to the floor. He gets up slowly, clutching at the bar for balance.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Perhaps you've had enough to drink."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't be so hard on yourself. You didn't mean for this to happen."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You can't hide in here. You'll have to face her sooner or later."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That you're a terrible father?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>He stares at his mug again and takes a quick drink. "I don't know what I'm going to tell Odda."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If I'd gotten stuck with a kid, I'd probably be here, too."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd turns to you with a snarl. "Damn you, I love my son. I love Odda, too." He puts his head in his hands and leans against the bar. "It just all seems so pointless now."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's no excuse to sit here. Get your ass out there and look for him."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You think I haven't tried? I've lived in Ondra's Gift all my life. When someone's been missing this long..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There's a lot of things I never meant to happen."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack] "Why don't I put you out of your misery now?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How can you get drunk at a time like this? Your child is missing!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I heard about Derrin. Are you okay?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd turns the mug in his hands. "No. Not at all."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd buries his face in his hands. "It's not like that."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You think I don't know that?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd squeezes his eyes shut. "You wouldn't say that if you really knew the kind of father I've been."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack] "Yes. And now I know you can't be trusted to look after your daughter, either."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank Node 54</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>"At least you didn't let it get in the way of your busy drinking schedule."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And you sit here still?" She snorts.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Just leave me alone."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why don't you just take one of them stools over there?" He swats at the air in your general direction. "Nowhere else for me to go. Not with the wife in a state and my boy... my...." His face freezes with a stricken expression, and he turns back to the bar, muttering into his drink.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>61</ID>
      <DefaultText>Weyd looks into the mug between his hands. "That's it, then. There really is no going back. I failed my son."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>62</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm going to go look for him, anyway."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>